QUESTIONS
1. What are the units of slope gradient?
   https://int-data.neonscience.org/api/v0/locations/STER_003.basePlot.bgc.21

STANDARD_PLOT_PROPS (locationProperties)
  'Value for Plot subtype' - string e.g. 'basePlot'
  'Value for Plot type' - string e.g. 'distributed' or 'tower'
  'Value for Maximum elevation' - float in meters
  'Value for Minimum elevation' - float in meters
  'Value for National Land Cover Database (2001)' - string
  'Value for Plot dimensions' - string e.g. '40m x 40m',
  'Value for Plot size' - float in meters^2
  'Value for Slope aspect' - float - compass degrees the slope faces
  'Value for Slope gradient' - float - ???
  'Value for Soil type order' - string e.g. 'Mollisols'

  locationDecimalLatitude, locationDecimalLongitude, locationElevation (floats)
  points use locationElevation, polygons use min/max elevation from props

Tower
  type: 'TOWER' (prop: locationType)
  point
  no props
  count children of type 'LEVEL'
  
Hut
  type: 'HUT'
  point
  no props

Megapit
  type: 'MEGAPIT'
  point
  no props

Soil Plots
  type: 'SOIL_PLOT'
  polygon (locationPolygon)
  Inspect children locationDescriptions (in hierarchy) to get measurements, bar 'Not Used'

Terrestrial Base Plots
  type: 'OS Plot - all'
  Split locationName on '.', take first as PLOT_ID (e.g. STER_035.basePlot.all)
  Inspect (do not fetch) all siblings with the same PLOT_ID and PLOT_TYPE === 'basePlot'
    Split locationName on '.', take last as EXTENSION (e.g. STER_035.basePlot.bet)
    Match to TERRESTRIAL_BASE_PLOT_EXTENSIONS for info (keep list of exts, whatever)
  Fetch only .all for all STANDARD_PLOT_PROPS
  'Value for Plot type' for is 'distributed' or 'tower'
  Render as polygon using 'Value for Plot size'

Terrestrial Tower Phenology Plots
  type: 'OS Plot - phe'
  Fetch, get coords and STANDARD_PLOT_PROPS
  Render as polygon using 'Value for Plot size'

Terrestrial Distributed Tick Plots
  type: 'OS Plot - tck'
  Fetch, get coords and STANDARD_PLOT_PROPS
  Render as polygon using 'Value for Plot size'
  
Terrestrial Distributed Mammal Grids
  type: 'OS Plot - mam'
  Fetch, get coords and STANDARD_PLOT_PROPS
  Render as polygon using 'Value for Plot size'

Terrestrial Distributed Bird Grids
  type: 'OS Plot - brd'
  Fetch, get coords and STANDARD_PLOT_PROPS
  Render as polygon using 'Value for Plot size'
  
Terrestiral Distributed Mosquito Points
  type: 'OS Plot - mos'
  Also look for presence of 'OS Plot - mpt' with same PLOT_ID to confirm if present?
  Fetch get coords + elevation + props:
    'Value for National Land Cover Database (2001)' - string
    'Value for Slope aspect' - float - compass degrees the slope faces
    'Value for Slope gradient' - float - ???
    'Value for Soil type order' - string e.g. 'Mollisols'
  Render as point

